.SS Bindingmode
.PP
Creates a block which shows the binding mode in i3/sway compatible
window managers.
That is for example, when you press \f[C]$mod+r\f[R] to start resizing
windows.
.PP
When no special mode is active, i.e.\ the state is \f[C]default\f[R],
nothing will be shown.
If another mode is triggered, the block will show a button with the name
of the mode.
Clicking on the button will reset the mode to \f[C]default\f[R].
This block is mainly usefull in combination with the Workspaces block to
have a style-able replacement for the workspaces block provided with
i3-bar and swaybar.
.SS Examples
.PP
A bindingmode block:
.IP
.nf
\f[C]
[[block]]
block = \[dq]bindingmode\[dq]
\f[R]
