.SS Workspaces
.PP
Creates a block which shows the workspaces on i3/sway compatible window
managers.
This is mainly usefull in combination with the Bindingmode block to have
a style-able replacement for the workspaces block provided with i3-bar
and swaybar.
Like in the originals, clicking on a workspace changes focus to that
workspace.
.PP
Currently, the workspaces use the Idle, Good, Critical and Warning
colors to show which workspace has focus und/or the urgent hint set.
.SS Examples
.PP
Shows workspaces stripping their number.
Define your workspaces like
.IP
.nf
\f[C]
set $WS1    1 \[uF269]
bindsym $mod+F1  workspace $WS1
\&...
\f[R]
.fi
.IP
.nf
\f[C]
[[block]]
block = \[dq]workspaces\[dq]
strip_workspace_numbers = true
\f[R]
.fi
.PP
The workspaces block will use the workspace numbers for ordering but
will only show the symbols.
